@startuml activity-kbedit-undo
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the undo/redo model is a CONTROL FLOW over two stacks with a clear
'' do / undo / redo branch and the apply-cmd ⟷ invert duality; a coloured PlantUML activity expresses the
'' decision and the stack moves end-to-end.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Key-binding editor — undo / redo as a data-command lifecycle\n[:ui :kbedit] {:undo [] :redo []}

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #EAF6FF
  BorderColor #4C66AE
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF6D6
  DiamondBorderColor IPC_BORDER
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

start
:user edits a binding / set\n(capture C-x C-f, delete, rename, reorder, clone);
:build a data-command  cmd = {:op …};
:apply-cmd db cmd  →  db'; <<KEYMAP_TINT>>
:push cmd onto :undo,  clear :redo; <<APPDB_TINT>>
:install-active (live) + persist (debounced); <<IPC_TINT>>

if (Ctrl+Z  /  ↶ Undo?) then (yes)
  if (:undo non-empty?) then (yes)
    :cmd ← peek :undo\napply-cmd db (invert cmd) → db'; <<KEYMAP_TINT>>
    :pop :undo,  push cmd onto :redo; <<APPDB_TINT>>
    :install-active + persist; <<IPC_TINT>>
  else (empty)
    :no-op;
  endif
elseif (Ctrl+Shift+Z  /  ↷ Redo?) then (yes)
  if (:redo non-empty?) then (yes)
    :cmd ← peek :redo\napply-cmd db cmd → db'; <<KEYMAP_TINT>>
    :pop :redo,  push cmd onto :undo; <<APPDB_TINT>>
    :install-active + persist; <<IPC_TINT>>
  else (empty)
    :no-op;
  endif
else (no history key)
  :idle;
endif
stop

note right #FFF6D6
  Because :insert-set / :remove-set are mutual inverses that carry the removed set's
  cfg + index, **undoing a delete restores the set at its original position**.
  A real Ctrl+Shift+Z arrives as chord **C-Z** (Shift uppercases z); the redo
  listener accepts C-Z / C-S-z / C-y.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Step concept |
  |<#BC6EC5>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| apply-cmd / invert (kbedit-history) |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db :undo / :redo stacks |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| live install + persist |
endlegend
@enduml
